  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Check and replace connecting rod bearings"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Engine Removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000356",
          "label": "Engine Removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Transmission removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000544",
          "label": "Transmission removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Drive plate removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000545",
          "label": "Drive plate removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Cylinder head removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000372",
          "label": "Cylinder head removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Oil pan removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000389",
          "label": "Oil pan removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Oil pump removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000406",
          "label": "Oil pump removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Bearing cap Bridge/bearing cap removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582911_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Loosen the bearing cap bolts several times in numerical order and remove the bearing cap bridge and bearing cap."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The bearing cap bolts should not be loosened all at once, but several times diagonally from outside to inside.",
        "Before disassembling, check the mounting position of each component and mount them in the same position when installing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Remove connecting rod cap/con-rod bearing"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582912_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the connecting rod cap (A) and connecting rod bearing (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Connecting rod bearing Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582913_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Measurements must always be taken in the axial direction.",
        "Do not rotate the crankshaft."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Torque: 0.5 to 1.0 MPa"
          },
          {
            "text": "10N·m (1.0kgf·m)"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Tighten connecting rod bolts 90°. Remove the connecting rod cap and connecting rod bearing, and measure the crushed width of the plastigauge with the scale printed on the bag of the plastigauge."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Measurements should be taken at the most widely crimped point.",
        "If the standard value is exceeded, the connecting rod shall be enlarged, the pin shall be inspected for wear, and if there is no abnormality, the connecting rod shall be replaced with an undersized bearing using the connecting rod bearing identification chart and the oil clearance shall be measured again."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Std."
          },
          {
            "text": "0.020－0.038mm"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582914_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "7",
      "text": "Examine the mating marks on the crankshaft pin journal."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the mating mark is not visible, do not scrub with a wire brush, screwdriver, etc., but clean with washing oil, etc., and check."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582915_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "8",
      "text": "Examine the mating marks on the connecting rod."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the mating mark is not visible, do not scrub with a wire brush, screwdriver, etc., but clean with washing oil, etc., and check."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582916_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "9",
      "text": "The identification color (A) of connecting rod bearings is blue-black-brown-green-yellow-peach-red, in that order, with each bearing having a tolerance of every 0.003 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "markup",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Distinctive color",
