    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Connecting rod Bolt inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11677578_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Measure the outside diameter of the connecting rod bolt at two locations and determine the difference in outside diameters."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "A micrometer should be used for the measurement.",
        "Measurements shall be taken on all connecting rod bolts.",
        "If the difference in outside diameter is greater than the limit, the connecting rod bolts should be replaced."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Limit value: 1"
          },
          {
            "text": "0－0.05mm"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Connecting rod cap/conrod bearing mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582918_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install connecting rod cap (A) and connecting rod bearing (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "12. Connecting rod cap installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582919_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Align the connecting rod caps with the bottom dead center of each cylinder and then tighten temporarily."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When installing the connecting rod cap, be sure to align the mating marks (A) so as to avoid misorientation.",
        "Do not drop the thrust washer when rotating the crankshaft."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Torque: 0.5 to 1.0 MPa"
          },
          {
            "text": "10N·m (1.0kgf·m)"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582920_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Tighten connecting rod bolts 90°."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the specified tightening angle is exceeded when tightening the connecting rod bolts, remove the bolts and retighten them after performing the connecting rod bolt inspection procedure again."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "13. Bearing/Bearing Cap/Bearing Cap Bridge Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582921_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove old fluid packings, oil, and dirt from the cylinder block and No. 4 bearing cap (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When installing the bearing caps, they must be installed in the same position and orientation as in the assembled condition."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582922_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Apply Honda Genuine Liquid Packing 1216E to the cylinder block contact surface of the No. 4 bearing cap."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Apply liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 2.5 mm along the dashed line (A)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the liquid packing is left on for more than 4 minutes after application, do not install it as it is. Remove the packing once and reapply.",
        "Oil should be injected at least 30 minutes after installation.",
        "Do not touch the liquid packing-applied surface.",
        "Wipe off any fluid packing that protrudes from the crankshaft pulley and drive plate side.",
        "The engine should be started at least 3 hours after installation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "388_5.0_jpn_11582923_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Install the bearing, bearing cap, and bearing cap bridge, and tighten the bearing cap bolts in numerical order to 33 N-m (3.4 kgf-m)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "14. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When a new bearing is assembled, it should be broken in at idle for 10-20 minutes to prevent separation or seizure of the bearing if the rotation is increased too rapidly."
      ]
    }
  ],
